de.hsos.ecs.richwps.wpsmonitor.data.dataaccess

Interface DataAccess<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of Entity which the DataAccess implementation should take care of
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    QosDataAccess, WpsDataAccess, WpsProcessDataAccess
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    QosDao, WpsDao, WpsProcessDao

    public interface DataAccess<T>
extends AutoCloseable
    Primary Interface for DataAccess-Objects
    Author:
    Florian Vogelpohl

    • Method Detail

      • find

        T find(Object primaryKey)
        Tries to find an Object in the Database with the given primary key. Otherwhise null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        primaryKey - The primary key of the Object. Typically a Long value.
        Returns:
        The Object that match the given primarykey. Otherwise null is returned if no result is found.

      • persist

        Boolean persist(T entityObject)
        Tries to persist the given object.
        Parameters:
        entityObject - Entity instance
        Returns:
        True if the object is sucessfully persisted, otherwise false will be returned

      • update

        T update(T entityObject)
        Updates the given Object in the Database.
        Parameters:
        entityObject - Entity instance
        Returns:
        The updated object.

      • remove

        void remove(T o)
        Removed o from Database
        Parameters:
        o - Entity instance

      • get

        List<T> get(Range range)
        Selects all elements in the given range [offset, count]
        Parameters:
        range - Range instance
        Returns:
        All found elements, otherwise null or an empty list
        See Also:
        Range

      • commit

        Boolean commit()
        Commit the transaction. If an exception occours, then commit will return false. An Exception can occour if a primary key violation is happened or something else
        Returns:
        If an exception has been thrown

      • rollback

        void rollback()
        Rolls the transacton back

      • setAutoCommit

        void setAutoCommit(Boolean value)
        By default all actions will be autocommited.
        Parameters:
        value - false to deactivate autocommit, otherwise true

      • close

        void close()
        Should be called if the DataAccess is no longer needed. The specific implementation of the DataAccess interface need to decide what is to do.
        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
